Shadow Wing::

She looked at him. Was he really going to kill her? She twisted and turned, 
but he had a good hold on her.  She knew that his wold instints were taking 
over.  She had to react fast.  She let out an ear splitting screek. Then she 
reached with her tallon and scratched his arm, the one that held her.  She 
flapped her wings as hard as she could.  She was flapping her wings hard 
enough to almost lift him off the ground.
"The game isn't over yet. Kill me and it will be."
She realized that if he didn't span out of it, the wolf in him would kill 
her. She tried to claw at his face with her talons.

Lunarpine stopped suddenly, smelling the crow realizing the irony of
the owls catch. All he could think how he'd under reacted to her
trick.

The wolf transformed to bot again and lunged forward pinning the owl
to the ground."You let your gaurd down before confirming the game was
over." He raised a claw to the owls throat. "So what am I going to do
with a dead carcas?" He lifted Shadow Wing into the ait claw still poised 
for the kill.
